        Description copied from class: StateModelChecker
        Model check an expression and return a vector result values over all states. Information about states and model constants should be attached to the model. For other required info (labels, reward structures, etc.), use the methods #setModulesFile and #setPropertiesFile to attach the original model/properties files.
        Overrides:
        checkExpression in class StateModelChecker
        statesOfInterest - a set of states for which results should be calculated (null = all states). The calculated values for states not of interest are arbitrary and should to be ignored.
